ABOUT 

This is a TextMate plugin that enables you to edit files in fullscreen-mode. It adds a submenu Window->Fullscreen with the default mapping to CTRL+ALT+CMD+. to activate fullscreen mode.

INSTALL 

To install it simply download the newest zip from the downloads page, unzip it and double-click the Fullscreen.tmplugin file and you're ready to go.

FAQ

Q: I have the plugin working, however when i hit the shortcut the window does not go into fullscreen but the background gradually gets darker the more i hit the shortcut.

A: One of the Universial Access shortcuts stealing the focus. Go into System Preferences -> Keyboard -> Universal Access and de-select the Increase contrast shortcut.